docs.abstract: An expanding coalition of Native Americans, liberal activists and Democrats in Congress are demanding an American Indian Interior secretary, and they want Deb Haaland.
docs.snippet: An expanding coalition of Native Americans, liberal activists and Democrats in Congress are demanding an American Indian Interior secretary, and they want Deb Haaland.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A coalition of Democrats, Native Americans and liberal activists is urging President-elect Joseph R. Biden Jr. to nominate one of Congress’s first Native American women to head the Interior Department, putting an American Indian in control of vast swaths of the continent and the Bureau of Indian Affairs.

headline.main: A Push Emerges for the First Native American Interior Secretary
headline.print_headline: Group Pushes Native American for Interior Post

docs.abstract: President Trump and his lawyers are engaged in a spectacle that would be funny if it weren’t so dangerous, and if the stakes weren’t so high.
docs.snippet: President Trump and his lawyers are engaged in a spectacle that would be funny if it weren’t so dangerous, and if the stakes weren’t so high.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump, who said there would be so much winning in his White House that Americans would grow tired of it, is of a different mind-set these days. He is not, apparently, tired of losing.

headline.main: Trump’s Legal Team Sets a Precedent for Lowering the Bar
headline.print_headline: Trump’s Legal Team Sets a Precedent for Lowering the Bar

docs.abstract: A few top Republicans called for a smooth transition, but the critical mass of the party remained silent as President Trump continued to try to subvert the popular vote and falsely claim he won re-election.
docs.snippet: A few top Republicans called for a smooth transition, but the critical mass of the party remained silent as President Trump continued to try to subvert the popular vote and falsely claim he won re-election.
docs.lead_paragraph: Nearly two weeks after President-elect Joseph R. Biden Jr. was declared the winner of the election, leading congressional Republicans remain unwilling to recognize his victory, keeping silent on Friday even in the face of President Trump’s increasingly brazen attempts to subvert the results.

headline.main: Republicans in Congress Stay Largely in Line Behind Trump
headline.print_headline: Few Voices Breaking From G.O.P.’s Wall of Silence Over Trump’s Defeat

docs.abstract: Donald Trump Jr., the president’s son, tested positive for the coronavirus at the beginning of the week and has been isolating since Monday, a spokesman for Mr. Trump said on Friday.
docs.lead_paragraph: Donald Trump Jr., the president’s son, tested positive for the coronavirus at the beginning of the week and has been isolating since Monday, a spokesman for Mr. Trump said on Friday.

headline.main: Donald Trump Jr. tests positive for coronavirus. He has been isolating since Monday.

docs.abstract: The president’s allies quickly closed ranks behind Sidney Powell and her pro-Trump conspiracy theory, accusing the Fox host of betrayal.
docs.snippet: The president’s allies quickly closed ranks behind Sidney Powell and her pro-Trump conspiracy theory, accusing the Fox host of betrayal.
docs.lead_paragraph: For more than a week, a plain-spoken former federal prosecutor named Sidney Powell made the rounds on right-wing talk radio and cable news, facing little pushback as she laid out a conspiracy theory that Venezuela, Cuba and other “communist” interests had used a secret algorithm to hack into voting machines and steal millions of votes from President Trump.

headline.main: Tucker Carlson Dared Question a Trump Lawyer. The Backlash Was Quick.
headline.print_headline: Fox News Host Faces Backlash for Questioning A Trump Lawyer’s Claims

docs.abstract: The Met is offering many employees their first paycheck in months if their unions agree to long-term cuts.
docs.snippet: The Met is offering many employees their first paycheck in months if their unions agree to long-term cuts.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Metropolitan Opera has offered to start paying many employees who have been furloughed without pay since April up to $1,500 a week in exchange for new union contracts that include long-term pay cuts, the company’s general manager said in a meeting with staff on Friday.

headline.main: Met Opera Seeks Pay Cuts in Exchange for Pandemic Paychecks

docs.abstract: A new rule would base the price Medicare pays for certain drugs on the lowest price paid among similar countries. But a rushed process means legal challenges are likely.
docs.snippet: A new rule would base the price Medicare pays for certain drugs on the lowest price paid among similar countries. But a rushed process means legal challenges are likely.
docs.lead_paragraph: Health officials on Friday finalized a policy that would base the price Medicare pays for certain drugs on the lowest price paid in some other developed nations. It is the most ambitious of several drug-pricing rules issued in the final months of President Trump’s term, but is likely to be vulnerable to legal challenges.

headline.main: A Final Try by Trump to Cut Drug Prices May Stumble in Court
headline.print_headline: Final Try by Trump  To Cut Drug Prices  May End in Court

byline.original: By Margot Sanger-Katz and Noah Weiland

docs.abstract: Trump’s Treasury secretary said Congress wanted key economic supports to end by Dec. 31, a view he expressed only after the vote count in the presidential election.
docs.snippet: Trump’s Treasury secretary said Congress wanted key economic supports to end by Dec. 31, a view he expressed only after the vote count in the presidential election.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin broke sharply with the Federal Reserve this week, choosing to end a variety of programs aimed at helping markets, businesses and municipalities weather the pandemic and asking the central bank to return the funds earmarked to support those efforts.

headline.main: Mnuchin Cites Principles in Clawing Back Fed Money. Democrats See Politics.
headline.print_headline: Mnuchin Cites Principles As Democrats See Politics

docs.lead_paragraph: In a chaotic effort to overturn the election results, President Trump and lawyers representing his campaign have spent weeks claiming without convincing proof that rampant voter fraud corrupted vote tallies in many battleground states.
